7. GAMIFICATION UI PATTERNS
================================================================================

PROVEN PATTERNS
---------------
- Points/XP: Each completed task earns XP, accumulates toward levels
- Badges/Achievements: Milestone-based rewards (10 tasks, first streak, etc.)
- Streaks: Daily consistency motivation (Duolingo achieves 55% retention)
- Leaderboards: Social competition (optional, privacy-respecting)
- Challenges: Time-limited goals for engagement
- Progress Bars: Fill up as tasks complete, visual satisfaction
- Leveling: XP thresholds unlock new features/themes/content

HABITICA MODEL (30% MORE DAILY HABITS COMPLETED)
-------------------------------------------------
- Converts daily tasks into RPG quests
- Users gain XP for completing real-world activities
- Character grows and evolves with consistency
- Party/guild system for social accountability

DUOLINGO MODEL (55% RETENTION VIA STREAKS)
------------------------------------------
- Streak counter is central to the experience
- XP rewards with 500M+ registered users
- Daily goals with visual progress
- Celebratory animations on milestones

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX:
  * XP System:
    - Complete task: +10 XP (+ bonus for on-time, energy-aligned)
    - Focus session: +25 XP per completed pomodoro
    - Streak day: +50 XP (scaling with streak length)
    - Channel reminder responded to: +5 XP
  * Levels: Unlock themes, sounds, content categories
    - Level 1-10: Apprentice (basic)
    - Level 11-25: Achiever (unlock custom themes)
    - Level 26-50: Master (unlock premium sounds)
    - Level 51+: Unjynxed (ultimate status, special badge)
  * Achievements: Glass trophy cards with gold accents
    - "First Unjynx" - Complete first task
    - "Streak Starter" - 3-day streak
    - "Fire Keeper" - 30-day streak
    - "Unjynx Master" - 100-day streak
    - "Channel Surfer" - Use 5+ reminder channels
    - Industry-specific achievements for each mode
  * Daily Challenges: "Complete 5 tasks before noon" type challenges
  * Visual: XP bar at top of home screen, subtle gold fill animation

================================================================================
8. ONBOARDING FLOWS THAT CONVERT
================================================================================

CRITICAL STATISTICS
-------------------
- 77% of daily active users stop using app within FIRST 3 DAYS
- Android Day 1 retention: 22.6% | iOS Day 1 retention: 25.6%
- Structured onboarding increases retention by 50%
- Interactive onboarding: 50% higher activation than static tutorials
- Personalized onboarding playlists: 41% higher completion
- Apps explaining value before features: 45% more users retained
- Just-in-time tooltips: 30% higher retention
- Social proof in onboarding: 30% better conversion

TOP PATTERNS FOR 2025-2026
---------------------------
1. Progressive Onboarding: Gradually introduce features as users explore
2. Personalization Upfront: Theme, goals, content selection
3. Interactive: Hands-on experience with key features immediately
4. Trial-First: Try core features before registration
5. Just-in-Time: Tooltips triggered by behavior, not time
6. Social Proof: Testimonials and user counts
7. 3-7 steps maximum for initial flow
8. Demonstrate value quickly, features second

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX:
  Step 1: "What is Your Vibe?" - Choose dark theme variant (Midnight, Eclipse, Aurora)
  Step 2: "What Matters Most?" - Select 3 primary categories (Work, Health, Creative, etc.)
  Step 3: "How Should We Reach You?" - Pick reminder channels (WhatsApp, Telegram, Push, etc.)
  Step 4: "Your Industry" - Optional industry mode selection
  Step 5: "Create Your First Task" - Interactive, hands-on
  Step 6: "Daily Wisdom" - Preview content delivery with quote card
  Step 7: "You are Unjynxed" - Celebration animation, streak starts NOW

  Key Principles:
  * Show value in Step 5 (creating a task shows the core experience)
  * Step 3 is our unique differentiator - show it early
  * Celebration at the end creates positive emotional anchor
  * Skip option always available but progress shown ("5 of 7")
  * Each step has subtle parallax animation transition
  * Purple -> Gold gradient progress bar across top

================================================================================
9. DARK MODE PREMIUM DESIGN
================================================================================

CORE PRINCIPLES
---------------
- Never use pure black (#000000) - use dark grays (#1b1b1b, #222222, #242424)
- Never use pure white (#FFFFFF) text - use off-white/light gray for comfort
- Surface system with layered elevations (base, raised, overlay)
- Separate layers by subtle lightness shifts, not heavy borders
- Dark palettes feel "premium," "focused," "cinematic"
- Glass-like UI effects enhanced by dark mode
- Subtle gradients and neon-style highlights add depth
- Cleaner layouts, reduced text, high-impact visuals
- Dark mode enhances glassmorphism - blur + translucency look best on dark

SURFACE HIERARCHY (LIGHTEST = HIGHEST ELEVATION)
-------------------------------------------------
- Base surface: #121212 to #1a1a1a (main background)
- Surface 1: #1e1e1e to #242424 (cards, list items)
- Surface 2: #2a2a2a to #303030 (raised cards, modals)
- Surface 3: #353535 to #3c3c3c (dialogs, popups)
- Overlay: rgba(255,255,255,0.05) to rgba(255,255,255,0.12)

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX COLOR SYSTEM:
  Background base: #0D0B14 (very dark purple-black)
  Surface 1: #16122A (dark purple - cards)
  Surface 2: #1E1838 (medium dark purple - raised elements)
  Surface 3: #2A2347 (lighter purple - dialogs)

  Primary accent: #C9A84C (muted gold)
  Primary bright: #FFD700 (pure gold - sparingly)
  Secondary: #7B5EA7 (medium purple)
  Tertiary: #4ECDC4 (teal - for contrast/breaks)

  Text primary: #E8E6F0 (off-white with purple tint)
  Text secondary: #9B95B0 (muted lavender)
  Text on accent: #1A1525 (dark purple on gold backgrounds)

  Success: #4CAF50 (green)
  Warning: #FFB74D (amber)
  Error: #EF5350 (red)

  Glass effect: rgba(30, 24, 56, 0.6) with backdrop-filter: blur(16px)
  Glass border: rgba(201, 168, 76, 0.15) (subtle gold edge glow)

