  * Each setting section:
    - Glassmorphic card with purple surface
    - Icon in gold accent for each item
    - Smooth expand/collapse animations
    - Toggle switches with gold accent when ON
    - Haptic feedback on toggle

================================================================================
13. UNIQUE UI PATTERNS NOBODY ELSE DOES
================================================================================

AMBIENT SOUND VISUALIZER
-------------------------
Current state of art:
- Web Audio API for real-time frequency analysis (FFT)
- Frequency spectrum sliced into 64 bands (23Hz - 12,023Hz)
- Grouped into bass, mids, treble, highs
- Canvas-based real-time visualization
- Waveform display with microphone input support

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX:
  * During focus sessions, show a subtle audio waveform visualizer:
    - Thin animated line at bottom of screen
    - Responds to ambient sound in real-time
    - Colors shift based on sound type (nature=green, lo-fi=purple, rain=blue)
    - Minimal CPU impact - use simplified FFT with 16 bands
    - Can be toggled off in settings
  * This is UNIQUE - no productivity app does this

SOCIAL MEDIA CHANNEL PICKER
----------------------------
Current state: Omnichannel messaging platforms exist but none in task/reminder apps

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX:
  * "Reminder Channels" picker - this IS our unique feature:
    - Horizontal scrollable chip bar with platform icons
    - Each chip: platform icon + name + connection status
    - Connected: full color icon | Disconnected: grayscale
    - Tap to toggle channel for this specific reminder
    - Long-press to configure channel settings
    - Visual: glassmorphic chips with platform brand color accents
    - Priority order: drag to reorder escalation chain
    - Preview: "This reminder will reach you via:" with channel flow diagram
  * Escalation visualization:
    - Timeline showing: Push (immediate) -> WhatsApp (5min) -> SMS (15min) -> Call (30min)
    - Each step connected by animated dotted line
    - Gold highlight on active step

INDUSTRY MODE SELECTOR
-----------------------
No productivity app offers industry-specific modes

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX:
  * Full-screen mode picker during setup + accessible from settings:
    - Grid of glassmorphic cards, each representing an industry
    - Each card has:
      * Industry icon (custom illustrated, 3D-style)
      * Industry name
      * Brief description: "Optimized for [industry] workflows"
      * Preview of what changes (task templates, terminology, defaults)
    - Selected card: gold border glow + "Active" badge
    - Switching modes: smooth transition animation
    - Industries: Legal, Healthcare, Dev Teams, Education, Construction, Real Estate, Finance, HR, Marketing, Family, Students
    - Each mode changes: terminology, templates, default categories, AI suggestions, content themes

RITUAL/HABIT TRACKING UI
-------------------------
Key patterns from research:
- Calendar grid showing streaks (GitHub-style heatmap)
- Single-tap to mark habit "done" - frictionless
- Immediate visual feedback on toggle
- Color customization per habit
- Progress visible on home screen

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX "RITUALS":
  * Not "habits" - call them "Rituals" for brand differentiation
  * Ritual card design:
    - Glassmorphic card with habit icon + name
    - Circular mini-ring showing today progress
    - Streak count with flame icon
    - Single tap: mark complete with satisfying animation
    - Gold fill animation on completion
  * Weekly ritual grid:
    - 7 columns (days) x N rows (rituals)
    - Filled cells glow with category color
    - Empty cells: subtle outline
    - Current day column: gold border highlight
  * Monthly heatmap view:
    - GitHub-style grid for each ritual
    - Color intensity = consistency percentage
    - Purple gradient (light = low, dark = high consistency)
  * "Ritual Chain" visualization:
    - Connected chain links showing consecutive days
    - Breaking a chain: dramatic visual + encouraging message
    - Longest chain displayed prominently

================================================================================
14. COLOR PSYCHOLOGY - MIDNIGHT PURPLE + GOLD
================================================================================

PURPLE PSYCHOLOGY
-----------------
- Commonly associated with: royalty, luxury, creativity, power
- Midnight purple: mystery, elegance, sophistication
- Evokes introspection and creativity
- Encourages deep thought and imagination
- Soft/cool purples: balanced, soothing yet polished
- Perfect for productivity + creativity intersection
- Relevant in fintech and productivity where clarity and trust are essential

GOLD PSYCHOLOGY
---------------
- Warm, metallic contrast that enhances richness
- Easiest way to add "premium" perception without changing layout/typography
- Signals: achievement, value, success, warmth
- Sparingly used = maximum impact (10% rule)

PURPLE + GOLD COMBINATION
--------------------------
- Creates instant luxury perception
- Appears in luxury hospitality and premium retail
- Optimal ratio: 70% purple/dark, 20% neutral, 10% gold maximum
- Gold best used for: accent interactions, achievements, CTAs, selected states
- Purple best used for: backgrounds, surfaces, brand identity
- Complementary palette adds: teal (#4ECDC4) for freshness, white/off-white for text

SPECIFIC HEX RECOMMENDATIONS FOR UNJYNX
-----------------------------------------
Primary Purple Palette:
  #0D0B14 - Deepest background (near-black with purple)
  #16122A - Card surfaces
  #1E1838 - Raised surfaces
  #2A2347 - Dialogs/modals
  #3D3566 - Borders/dividers
  #7B5EA7 - Secondary accent
  #9B7FCC - Lighter interactive elements
  #C4B0E8 - Highlighted text

Gold Accent Palette:
  #FFD700 - Pure gold (celebrations, achievements only)
  #C9A84C - Primary gold accent (buttons, active states)
  #A8893D - Muted gold (secondary accents)
  #7A6330 - Dark gold (pressed states)
  #FFF1CC - Light gold (text on dark surfaces, sparingly)

Supporting Colors:
  #4ECDC4 - Teal (breaks/rest, secondary actions)
  #FF6B6B - Coral red (errors, urgent, delete)
  #4CAF50 - Green (success, completed)
  #FFB74D - Amber (warnings, medium priority)
  #42A5F5 - Blue (information, links)

================================================================================
15. ANIMATION PATTERNS & MICRO-INTERACTIONS
================================================================================

LOTTIE vs RIVE (2025-2026)
---------------------------
LOTTIE:
  - JSON-based animations from After Effects via Bodymovin
  - Timeline-based, plays predefined sequences
  - ~17 FPS on both JS and UI threads
  - Interactivity limited to play/pause/loop/seek
  - Huge library of pre-made animations (LottieFiles)
  - Late 2025: Added State Machine + AI generation capabilities
  - Best for: simple decorative animations, loading states, celebrations

RIVE:
  - State Machine for complex interactive graphics
  - ~60 FPS on both JS and UI threads (3.5x faster)
  - Responds to user inputs and data in real-time
  - Vector Feathering: soft glows/shadows without blur performance hit
  - Duolingo uses Rive: 15x reduction in file size
  - Best for: interactive UI elements, mascots, state-driven animations

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX:
  Use BOTH strategically:
  * Rive for: Interactive elements (timer ring, XP bar, streak flame, ghost icon, energy meter)
  * Lottie for: Celebration animations (task complete, achievement unlock, streak milestone)

FLUTTER-SPECIFIC ANIMATION PATTERNS
-------------------------------------
Hero Animations (Shared Element Transitions):
  - Widget smoothly animates between screens
  - Maintains appearance and size during transition
  - Creates continuity and visual coherence
  - Use for: Task card -> Task detail, Quote card -> Full screen, Profile pic -> Profile page

Custom Page Transitions (PageRouteBuilder):
  - Slide, fade, scale, rotate combinations
  - Tween + Curve for custom easing
  - Use for: All navigation transitions (consistent feel)

CustomPainter for Progress Rings:
  - SweepGradient shader for colorful progress
  - canvas.drawArc() starting from top (-pi/2)
  - AnimationController + SingleTickerProviderStateMixin
  - Use for: Timer ring, XP ring, UNJYNX Rings dashboard

HAPTIC FEEDBACK IN FLUTTER
---------------------------
  Built-in HapticFeedback class:
  - HapticFeedback.lightImpact() - task complete checkbox
  - HapticFeedback.mediumImpact() - drag start, reorder
  - HapticFeedback.heavyImpact() - delete confirmation, mode switch
  - HapticFeedback.selectionClick() - selection changes, toggles

  Use haptics for:
  - Task completion (light)
  - Drag and drop (medium on grab, light on release)
  - Timer start/stop (medium)
  - Achievement unlock (heavy + vibrate pattern)
  - Ghost mode activate (heavy + sustained)
  - Swipe actions threshold crossed (selection click)
  - Pull to refresh (selection click)

SPECIFIC MICRO-INTERACTION CATALOG FOR UNJYNX
----------------------------------------------
1. Task Complete: Checkbox fills with gold, line strikes through with "swiggly" animation (inspired by Superlist), confetti burst (Lottie), +XP floats up
2. Task Create: Card slides in from bottom, slight bounce, haptic light
3. Task Delete: Card shrinks and fades with red tint, haptic medium
4. Streak Milestone: Full-screen Lottie celebration, streak number scales up, flame intensifies
5. Level Up: Rive animation of XP ring overflowing, new level badge reveals
6. Channel Connected: Platform icon pulses green, status dot appears, haptic selection
7. Timer Start: Ring illuminates segment by segment, ambient sound fades in
8. Timer Complete: Ring fills gold, gentle pulse, achievement sound
9. Ghost Mode Enter: Screen dims, UI chrome fades, background transitions to ambient visual
10. Ghost Mode Exit: Reverse of enter, stats overlay fades in
11. Pull to Refresh: Custom Lottie pulling animation (ghost stretching)
12. Quote Swipe: Card physics-based swipe with parallax layers
13. Industry Mode Switch: Current mode card flips/morphs into new mode
14. Reminder Escalation: Animated timeline showing channel progression

================================================================================
16. TYPOGRAPHY TRENDS & FONT PAIRINGS
================================================================================

2025-2026 TRENDS
-----------------
- Variable fonts: new standard (adjust weight/width/slant on the fly)
- Readable type is mandatory (high contrast, larger x-heights, clear spacing)
- Big, expressive headlines with custom fonts
- Deliberate typeface choices that match brand personality
- Typography making digital experiences more human and adaptable

TOP FONT RECOMMENDATIONS
--------------------------
Figtree: Contemporary sans-serif, combines friendliness with legibility
General Sans: Elegance with slightly extended characters, prevents user fatigue
Magisans: Modern geometric sans-serif for clarity and precision
Manrope + Inter: Clear, low-friction reading at any size (fintech/productivity)

FONT PAIRING STRATEGIES
------------------------
- Simple body font + more expressive headline font = balance
- Variable fonts reduce file sizes and improve performance
- Prioritize: high contrast, larger x-heights, clear spacing
- Test on actual devices (not just design tools)

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX:

  Primary System (UI):
    Headlines: "General Sans" (Variable) - elegant, slightly extended, modern
    Body: "Inter" (Variable) - most readable UI font, Google Fonts
    Mono: "JetBrains Mono" - for timer display, code-like elements

  Content System (Quotes/Content):
    Quote text: "Playfair Display" or "Cormorant Garamond" - elegant serif
    Quote attribution: "General Sans" italic

  Hierarchy:
    Display (quotes, big numbers): 32-48sp, Playfair Display, light weight
    H1 (screen titles): 28sp, General Sans, semibold
    H2 (section headers): 22sp, General Sans, medium
    H3 (card titles): 18sp, General Sans, medium
    Body: 16sp, Inter, regular
    Body small: 14sp, Inter, regular
    Caption: 12sp, Inter, medium
    Overline: 10sp, General Sans, semibold, ALL CAPS, letter-spacing: 1.5

  Dark Theme Typography Notes:
    - Use font weight 400 (regular) for body, not 300 (light) - light text on dark bg needs more weight
    - Letter-spacing slightly increased (+0.15 to +0.5) for readability on dark backgrounds
    - Line height: 1.5x for body text, 1.2x for headlines
    - Off-white text (#E8E6F0) never pure white

================================================================================
17. FLUTTER / MATERIAL DESIGN 3 PATTERNS
================================================================================

MATERIAL 3 AS DEFAULT
----------------------
- Flutter 3.16+ uses Material 3 by default
- useMaterial3: true (already default)
- Dynamic Color: Android 12+ matches wallpaper colors
- Seed color generates harmonious color scheme automatically

COLOR SCHEME FROM SEED
-----------------------
- Set colorSchemeSeed in ThemeData to generate full scheme
- One seed color -> complete harmonious palette
- For UNJYNX: Use midnight purple (#2A2347) as primary seed
- Override specific roles for gold accent colors

NEW COLOR ROLES (Flutter Breaking Change)
------------------------------------------
- Primary, onPrimary, primaryContainer, onPrimaryContainer
- Secondary, onSecondary, secondaryContainer, onSecondaryContainer
- Tertiary (contrasting accents) - use for teal/gold
- Surface, onSurface, surfaceContainerLowest through surfaceContainerHighest
- Tonal elevation: surface color takes tint from primary based on elevation

TONAL ELEVATION (CRITICAL FOR DARK THEME)
------------------------------------------
- Material 3 represents elevation using tonal color overlays
- Not shadows (those are M2) - tonal shifts
- Higher elevation = more prominent tone from primary
- Creates depth without heavy shadows
- Perfect for glassmorphism approach (tonal + blur)

FLUTTER GLASSMORPHISM IMPLEMENTATION
--------------------------------------
Core widgets: BackdropFilter + ClipRRect + Container

  ClipRRect(
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16),
    child: BackdropFilter(
      filter: ImageFilter.blur(sigmaX: 16, sigmaY: 16),
      child: Container(
        decoration: BoxDecoration(
          color: Colors.white.withOpacity(0.05),
          borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(16),
          border: Border.all(color: Colors.white.withOpacity(0.1)),
        ),
      ),
    ),
  )

  Performance notes:
  - Blur is expensive - limit to visible cards only
  - Bound blur with ClipRRect to limit repaint area
  - Avoid stacking multiple blur containers
  - Dark mode = wow effect (glow pops more)
  - No extra packages needed for basic glassmorphism

FLUTTER HERO ANIMATIONS
------------------------
- Wrap widgets in Hero(tag: 'uniqueTag') on both screens
- Flutter handles the animation automatically
- Use for task card -> detail, quote card -> fullscreen
- PageRouteBuilder for custom transition curves

FLUTTER HAPTICS
---------------
  import 'package:flutter/services.dart';
  HapticFeedback.lightImpact();
  HapticFeedback.mediumImpact();
  HapticFeedback.heavyImpact();
  HapticFeedback.selectionClick();

FLUTTER CUSTOM PROGRESS RINGS
-------------------------------
  CustomPaint + CustomPainter:
  - Use SweepGradient for gradient ring
  - canvas.drawArc(rect, -pi/2, 2*pi*progress, false, paint)
  - Animate with AnimationController + Tween
  - StrokeCap.round for smooth ring ends

RECOMMENDATION FOR UNJYNX FLUTTER THEME:
  ThemeData(
    useMaterial3: true,
    brightness: Brightness.dark,
    colorSchemeSeed: Color(0xFF2A2347), // midnight purple
    // Override specific roles:
    colorScheme: ColorScheme.dark(
      primary: Color(0xFFC9A84C), // gold
      onPrimary: Color(0xFF1A1525),
      secondary: Color(0xFF7B5EA7),
      tertiary: Color(0xFF4ECDC4),
      surface: Color(0xFF16122A),
      onSurface: Color(0xFFE8E6F0),
    ),
  )

